question: 海魚
sourceMnemonic: An <kanji>ocean</kanji> <kanji>fish</kanji> is simply an <vocabulary>ocean fish</vocabulary>. They also happen to be the most delicious kind of fish.
sourceReadingMnemonic:
This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.

Some people also use the kun'yomi readings, but it's much less common, and generally considered colloquial.
